[According to the above press release, 2 cattle holdings in NRW, recently affected by _M. bovis_, have been depopulated. One was addressed in the OIE report (in Meinerzhagen). The other one is a dairy farm in Froendenberg, engaged in the rearing of in-calf heifers for the 1st farm. The distance between the 2 is about 43 km (about 27 mi).

The laboratory diagnosis of "cattle tuberculosis" in cattle "older than 2 years" from Maerkicher Kreis (which is the holding in Meinerzhagen) was published by TSIS (Animal Diseases Information System, administered by the Federal Ministry of Food and Agriculture in tandem with the Friedrich-Loeffler-Institute). See at https://tsis.fli.de/Reports/Info_SO.aspx?ts=204&guid=b760ac4c-1703-4c54-b68f-11e8369ef2a2. - Mod.AS

